parameters.name: Start Time
parameters.description:
The start time of the data spectrum in UTC.
                                 The Start Time and Stop Time fields define
                                 the time range covered by the data spectrum.
                                 The format is YYYY-DDDTHH:MM:SS.SSS.

parameters.name: Stop Time
parameters.description:
The end time of the data spectrum in UTC.
                                 The Start Time and Stop Time fields define
                                 the time range covered by the data spectrum.
                                 The format is YYYY-DDDTHH:MM:SS.SSS.

parameters.name: Scan Index
parameters.description:
A pure number which ranges from 0 to 30 when the
                                 electron instrument is in the 1 sec/sweep mode and
                                 from 0 to 126 when the electron instrument is in the 4 sec/sweep mode.
                                 The scan is a decay sweep, which means that a low scan index
                                 value represents a large energy.  The Scan Index, Electron Energy,
                                 and Velocity fields describe the energy scan of the data.

parameters.name: Electron Energy
parameters.description:
The energy for each Scan Index, which depends on the 
                                 instrument configuration; therefore, the same scan index
                                 does not always correspond to the same energy value.
                                 The Scan Index, Electron Energy, and Velocity fields describe
                                 the energy scan of the data.

parameters.name: Velocity
parameters.description:
The electron energy converted into velocity.
                                 The Scan Index, Electron Energy, and Velocity
                                 fields describe the energy scan of the data.
